Description: Fragment of floor of Attic stamped black-glazed pottery open vase, probably a kantharos. Wholly glazed. Tight ring of four palmettes at centre of floor inside. Incised inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 591)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1247)
